org.archive.wayback.resourceindex.updater

Class LocalResourceIndexUpdater

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.archive.wayback.resourceindex.updater.LocalResourceIndexUpdater
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Shutdownable

    public class LocalResourceIndexUpdater
extends Object
implements Shutdownable
    Class which starts a background thread that repeatedly scans an incoming directory and merges files found therein(which are assumed to be in CDX format) with a BDBIndex. Optional configurations include: target directory where merged files are moved to (otherwise deleted) target directory where failed failed are moved(otherwise left in place) milliseconds between scans of the incoming directory(default 10000)

    $Date$, $Revision$
    Author:
    brad
